description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced nurse looking for a change in career direction, newly qualified or about to qualify? If you are and are interested in developing skills and experience in Vascular Speciality then we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are the vascular Hub for North West London and if you join us you will have the opportunity to develop skills and experience in: &lt;br /&gt;• Caring for Patient following Complex Bowel surgery&lt;br /&gt;• Caring for patient admitted via A &amp; E with a variety conditions such as bowel obstruction and appendicitis &lt;br /&gt;• Caring for patients following gynaecology procedures. &lt;br /&gt;• Caring for step down patient’s from ITU.&lt;br /&gt;• You will work as a part of Multidisciplinary Team and be supported by an excellent Clinical Practice Educator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are many learning opportunities available including managing the deteriorating patient, wound management, pain management, diabetes management, health promotion, patient education, complex discharge planning and sepsis treatment. Colorectal, general surgery and gynaecology nursing is highly rewarding and provides you with plenty of scope to develop further specialist skills and roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust is a high performing Trust with some of the best clinical outcomes in the country. We are ranked amongst best English Trust for mortality rates and CQC rates us overall Good. We also offer following benefits:&lt;br /&gt;• Mentorship from our dynamic supportive team&lt;br /&gt;• Comprehensive Preceptorship and individually tailored training.&lt;br /&gt;• Leadership skills for the talented and aspiring leaders of the future.&lt;br /&gt;• Internal Transfer Scheme &lt;br /&gt;• Accommodation &lt;br /&gt;• Nurseries and childcare vouchers&lt;br /&gt;• Keep Fit schemes and access to staff gym and swimming pool&lt;br /&gt;• Our hospitals are located close to many attractions with easy and fast transport links to central London&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paula Galvin - paula.galvin@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
